<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+{4}{y}=-{7}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{9}{x}-{7}{y}={76}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({3},-{7}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+{4}{y}=-{7}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}=-{7}-{\left({4}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{7}-{\left({4}{y}\right)}}}{{7}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{\left(\frac{{-{7}-{\left({4}{y}\right)}}}{{7}}\right)}+-{7}{y}={76}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{9}}{{7}}\cdot{\left(-{7}\right)}-\frac{{9}}{{7}}{\left({4}\right)}{y}+-{7}{y}={76}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}-{\left(-{5.1428571428571}\right)}{y}+-{7}{y}={76}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5.1428571428571}{y}+{\left(-{7}\right)}{y}={76}--{9}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{5.1428571428571}{y}+{\left(-{7}\right)}{y}={85}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{5.1428571428571}+{\left(-{7}\right)}\right)}{y}={85}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{12.142857142857}{y}={85}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{85}}{{-{{12.142857142857}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{7}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+{4}{\left(-{7}\right)}=-{7}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}+{\left(-{28}\right)}=-{7}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}=-{7}-{\left(-{28}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{7}{x}={21}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{21}}{{7}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={3}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({3},-{7}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

